<TITLE> Committee to report on pay hike by June 30 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jun 22 (bdnews24.com)A secretary-level committee tasked with making suggestions to implement the government-announced seventh pay commission recommendations for civil servants will submit report by June 30, the committee head said on Monday. Cabinet secretary Abdul Aziz told bdnews24.com that his committee has already discussed with representatives of the government employees and moved to finalise a report. The recommendations might include a 10:1 ratio to fix salaries. "The committee will soon hold another meeting to finalise the report and submit it to the prime minister," Aziz said. The committee has considered all possible aspects to prepare the report so that it could be implemented from July, the beginning month of the next fiscal year. bd
